14:[["$","p",null,{"children":"This is a sample piece. It exists to demonstrate the reading experience and show how different content elements render. Replace it with your first real piece whenever you're ready."}],"\n",["$","h2",null,{"children":"Headings and structure"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"Second-level headings create natural sections within a piece. They use the title scale — large enough to orient, small enough not to shout."}],"\n",["$","h3",null,{"children":"A third-level heading"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"Third-level headings are subtler — a weight shift rather than a size shift. Use them for fine-grained structure within a section, not as a replacement for good paragraph transitions."}],"\n",["$","h2",null,{"children":"Typography in body copy"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"Body text is set at 1rem with a line-height of 1.75. That's generous — intentionally so. Reading should feel unhurried."}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Bold"}]," is used sparingly, for genuine emphasis. ",["$","em",null,{"children":"Italic"}]," for titles, terms being introduced, or light stress. Neither should appear more than once or twice per section or they lose meaning."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["Links in body copy are ",["$","a",null,{"href":"#","target":"$undefined","rel":"$undefined","children":"underlined"}]," in the conventional sense — not just colored differently. This matters for readability and accessibility: color alone is not a reliable signal."]}],"\n",["$","h2",null,{"children":"Lists"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"An unordered list:"}],"\n",["$","ul",null,{"children":["\n",["$","li",null,{"children":"Ideas I'm exploring"}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":"Things I'm learning"}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":"Observations and curiosities"}],"\n"]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"An ordered list, for when sequence matters:"}],"\n",["$","ol",null,{"children":["\n",["$","li",null,{"children":"Understand the problem"}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":"Understand the constraints"}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":"Find the simplest solution that fits both"}],"\n"]}],"\n",["$","h2",null,{"children":"Blockquotes"}],"\n",["$","blockquote",null,{"children":["\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"The goal is not to be interesting to everyone, but to be genuinely useful to someone."}],"\n"]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"Blockquotes are set in a muted tone with a thin left border. Use them for external references, or for pulling out a sentence that deserves more space than a paragraph can give it."}],"\n",["$","h2",null,{"children":"Code"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["Inline ",["$","code",null,{"children":"code"}]," has a subtle background — readable without pulling too much visual weight."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"Code blocks use syntax highlighting:"}],"\n",["$","figure",null,{"data-rehype-pretty-code-figure":"","children":["$","pre",null,{"style":{"backgroundColor":"#22272e","color":"#adbac7"},"tabIndex":"0","data-language":"javascript","data-theme":"github-dark-dimmed","children":["$","code",null,{"data-language":"javascript","data-theme":"github-dark-dimmed","style":{"display":"grid"},"children":[["$","span",null,{"data-line":"","children":["$","span",null,{"style":{"color":"#768390"},"children":"// A short example"}]}],"\n",["$","span",null,{"data-line":"","children":[["$","span",null,{"style":{"color":"#F47067"},"children":"function"}],["$","span",null,{"style":{"color":"#DCBDFB"},"children":" readingTime"}],["$","span",null,{"style":{"color":"#ADBAC7"},"children":"("}],["$","span",null,{"style":{"color":"#F69D50"},"children":"content"}],["$","span",null,{"style":{"color":"#ADBAC7"},"children":") {"}]]}],"\n",["$","span",null,{"data-line":"","children":[["$","span",null,{"style":{"color":"#F47067"},"children":"  const"}],["$","span",null,{"style":{"color":"#6CB6FF"},"children":" words"}],["$","span",null,{"style":{"color":"#F47067"},"children":" ="}]